Backend — air_traffic.py (full rewrite of Stage 5 MVP):
- Trail history: air_trail table (per-aircraft, ring-buffer TRAIL_MAX=8 pts,
  TTL=3600s); upsert_trails() inserts on every refresh, load_trails() returns
  {icao24: [[lng,lat],...]} ordered oldest→newest for LineString rendering
- Improved AOI intersection: _aircraft_near_geom() replaces flat 0.5° pad:
  * Point AOI → haversine km check (default 30 km radius)
  * Polygon AOI → ray-casting point-in-polygon (no deps) + edge buffer
  * LineString AOI → per-segment corridor check + haversine to midpoint
  * Fallback → padded bbox
- Filter support: fetch_aircraft_filtered() for alt_min/alt_max/speed_min/callsign

Backend — main.py endpoint updates:
- POST /api/air/refresh: optional query params (alt_min, alt_max, speed_min, callsign);
  calls upsert_trails() after fetch; returns trails{} in response
- GET  /api/air/latest: now includes trails{} for current snapshot aircraft
- GET  /api/air/near-aois: accepts pad_km param (default 30.0); uses geometry-aware check
- GET  /api/air/trails: returns trail data, optional icao24 filter
- DB: air_trail table + index created on startup

Frontend — airLayer.js:
- Trail source (src-air-trail) + AIR_TRAIL_LAYER line layer added
- setAirTrails(map, trails, aircraft): builds LineString FeatureCollection,
  altitude-coded line color matching dot color scheme
- setAirVisibility() now covers trail layer too

Frontend — AircraftPanel.jsx:
- Filter panel (collapsible via ⊟ FILTERS button):
  callsign substring, alt_min/alt_max (metres), speed_min (m/s)
- Filters applied both client-side (display) and server-side (on next refresh)
- FILTERS* label when active filters present
- Trail badge in summary (count of aircraft with trail data)
- Trail point count shown in aircraft detail view
- ⇒ trail indicator on aircraft rows that have history

Frontend — MapView.jsx:
- airTrails prop + airTrailsRef added; setAirTrails called on init and in data effect
- aircraft+trail useEffect combined ([aircraft, airTrails] deps)

Frontend — App.jsx:
- handleAirRefresh(filters): passes filters to refreshAirTraffic(), stores trails
  in airSnapshot.trails; filter note in toast message
- airTrails={airSnapshot?.trails || {}} wired to MapView

Frontend — useApi.js:
- refreshAirTraffic(filters): builds URLSearchParams from filter object
- fetchAirNearAois(padKm): optional pad_km param
- fetchAirTrails(icao24): new endpoint wrapper

Build: npm run build ✓ (59 modules, 0 errors, 9.17s)
